ENTRY       EC 2.1.1.232                Enzyme
NAME        naringenin 7-O-methyltransferase;
            NOMT
CLASS       Transferases;
            Transferring one-carbon groups;
            Methyltransferases
SYSNAME     S-adenosyl-L-methionine:(2S)-5,7,4'-trihydroxyflavanone 7-O-methyltransferase
REACTION    S-adenosyl-L-methionine + (2S)-naringenin = S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + (2S)-sakuranetin [RN:R09791]
ALL_REAC    R09791
SUBSTRATE   S-adenosyl-L-methionine [CPD:C00019];
            (2S)-naringenin [CPD:C00509]
PRODUCT     S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine [CPD:C00021];
            (2S)-sakuranetin [CPD:C09833]
COMMENT     The enzyme is involved in the biosynthesis of the sakuranetin, an inducible defense mechanism of the plant Oryza sativa (Asian rice) against pathogen attack.
HISTORY     EC 2.1.1.232 created 2011
